lo., Oct, 27\u2014hP\u2014\nLouis D. Blauvelt, 63. Colorado\nstate highway engineer, who as p\nwar time army major planned ..nd\nbuilt a $40,000,000 toxic gas plant\nat Edgewater arsenal in Maryland\ndied here yesterday.\nAUTO ACCIDENT\nSTRAWN, Tex., Oct. 27\u2014(JP)\u2014\nJulius Schwasig and Leonce Rieu,\n21. both of Strawn. were instantly\nkilled yesterday when a light car\nin which they were riding collided\nwith two other automobiles on the\nhighway near here, and overturned.\nThree occupants of one of the other\ncars were slightly injured and were\ntreated at a Ranger hospital.\nSchwasig and Rleu, according tr\nreports, were attempting to pass\nanother car occupied by Mrs. and\nMrs. C, F. Waldrop and Mr. and\nMrs. H L. McKay, all of Marshall\nThe light car struck the rear o'.\nthe Marshall car. then crashed In\nto a machine driven by L. J. Heff\nner. who lives In California.\nRITES FOR EDITOR\nFORT WORTH. Oct. 21\u2014(/P)\nFuneral rites were set for this\nafternoon for Ned C. Record, 29\nsports editor of the Rectd-Tele\ngram since 1925. He died Srturday\nat 5:40 p. m. of penumonla that\nfollowed an emergency operation\nOct. 16 for appendicitis.\nFellow employes on the Star\nTelegram and Record-Telegram ex\npected to serve as pallbarers at the\nsendees at 3:30 p m. from St. Marv\u2019r\nCatholic church.\nLUFKIN KILLING\nLUFKIN. Oct. 21\u2014up)\u2014Tom Mur\nray. 30. jitney owner, was shot and\nkilled here yesterday on a down\ntown street. A meat cutter, resld\nin? at Jasper and formerly of\nLufkin, surrendered to *he sheriff\nInsull Is Purchaser\nOf Valley Orchard\nMartin J. insull, the multi-mil\nlionaire who. in company with\nother men of wealth, visited the\nValley recently, was so impressed\nwith thts section that he has\nbought a 12-acre citrus orchard as\nan investment and an experiment\nit was announced Monday.\nMr. Insull and a party of about\n20 men inspected the Rio Grande\nValley from Mission to Port Isabel\nwhile here, and although the\nweather was inclement during their\nvisit, they appreciated conditions\nhere and realized the brilliant fu\nture to such an extent that the\nleader decided to purchase an or\nchard. it was said today. It was\nfurther added that others of the\nparty may follow Mr Insull and\nbuy orchards for development.\nSubstitute Mother\nIs Not Wanted\nSubstitute mother wouldn\u2019t un\nderstand you. No mother equals\nyour own. So with your old tried\nand true remedy for constipated,\ntorpid liver, there is no substitute.\nCarter's Llftle Liver Pills, made of\ngenuine vegetable calomel, is old\nest liver remedy known. Take Car\nter\u2019s. enjoy free flowing bile for\nthorough system cleansing. Red\nbottles only. Take Carter\u2019s. Adv.\nBEWARE THE COUGH FROM\nCOLDS THAT HANG ON\nCoughs from t olds may lead to se\nrious trouble. You can stop them\ndow with Creomulsion. an emulsified\ncreosote that is pleasant to take.\nCreomulsion is a medical discovery\nwith two-fold action; it soothes and\nheals the inflamed membranes and in\nhibits germ growth.\nOf all known drugs creosote is rec\nognized by high medical authorities\nas one of the greatest healing agencies\nfor (ought from colds and bronchial\nj irritations. Creomulsion contains, in\naddition to creosote, other healing\nelements which soothe and heal the\ninflamed membranes and stop the ir\nritation, while the creosote goes on to\nthe vtomach. is absorbed into the\nblood, attacks the seat of the trouble\nand checks the growth of the germs.\nCreomulsion is guaranteed satisfac\ntory in the treatment of coughs from\ncolds, bronchitis and minor forms of\nbronchia] irritations, and is excellent\nfor building up the system after colds\nor flu. Money refunded if not re\nlieved after taking according to direc\ntions. Ask your druggist, (adr.)\nC REOMULS I ON\nFOR THE COUGH FROM COLDS THA T HANG ON\nFuneral Services\nFor Rio Hondo Child\n(Special to The Herald)\nHARLINGEN. Oct. 27.-Funeral\nservices for Joseph Harry Brannon\nseven-^nonths old son of Ir. and\nMrs. L M. Brannon, of Rio Hondo\nare to be held Monday afternoon\nat Thompson\u2019s chapel, with thf\nRev. C. H. Harrison, pastor ttv\nChristian church here officiatlna\nInterment will be In the Mont Met?\ncemetery. The child is survived bv\nhis parents, one brother and two\nsisters.\ni?\"i__\u25a0 i i\nNinety-two Bodies\nTaken From Mine\nSMYRNA. Asia Minor. Oct. 27.\u2014\n(jt)\u2014Torrenttal rains In Smyrna\nhave brought death to 30 persons\nand destroyed 220 houses. All elec\ntricity has been cut off by the\nseething torrents, which have raced\ndown the streets, carrying horses\nand carriages toward the sea\nThe governor, attempting to or\nganize rescue work, was almost\ncarried into the sea from his auto\nmobile.\nVannie Tilden\nHome Baking\n_4\nSomething Different\nI\nDelicious Home Baked\nPastry and Bread\nPhone 753\n509 Elizabeth Brownsville\nUnderstanding\nWhen our customers bring their fi\nnancial problems to the Merchants\u2019\nNational, we try to put ourselves\n\u201cin their shoes.*\u2019\nWe sincerely endeavor to consider\neach transaction from the other fel\nlow\u2019s point-of-view.\nCapital Stock:\nOriginally paid in ....$100,000.00\nIncreased from earnings 150,000.00 $250,000.00\nSurplus Fund, earned.. 275,000.00\nMERCHANTS'\nNATIONAL BANK\nBR.OW N 5 VILLE -TEXAS.*\n'-w\nONE WILL ALWAYS STAND OUT\n\nf\nI\ni\n\n!j\nMilder and\n-ij;\nj better taste!\nt\n1032-36 Elizabeth St. Brownsville, Texas\nBe Ready for That First Cold Night!\nWinter Bedding\nat Substantial Savings!\nAll wool blankets in fast colors\nSize 66x80\nPrice $5.90\nFine All-Wool\nBlankets\nBlock Plaids; All Vir\ngin Wool; Large Size,\n70x80\n$7.90\nBlock Plaid\nBlankets\nExtra lam aiae. 72x84 ioch*#|\nof fin# China cotton and mqpi\nWool; nteen bound. Wt, 5 !b*\n$3.98\nI __\nCottoB-aad-WaoI\nBlankets\nSelected Chin* cotton mixed\nwith smaC percent*** of Tirgin\nwool; block p!*fd#: mteen\nbound; 70x80 laches.\n$1.\nPlaid Caftan\nBlankets\nOutstanding value I Large sise\n